enum LcsErrorCode
 

Defines all possible kinds of location errors.

Enumerator:
LcsSystemFailure  Indicates a failure in the network.
LcsUnexpectedDataValue  Indicates that a parameter has an unexpected value, but type is OK.
LcsDataMissing  Indicates that an optional parameter that is required in this context is missing.
LcsFacilityNotSupported  Indicates that requested facility is not supported by the network.
LcsSsSubscriptionViolation  Indicates that requested Lcs SS violates the subscription restrictions.
LcsPosMethodFailure  Indicates that requested location information not obtained or assistance data transfer failed or Qos not met
LcsNoError  Indicates no error.
LcsTimeOut  Indicates that MO-LR is taking longer than the max response time.
LcsInternalError  Indicates that some internal error has occures.
LcsProviderNotAvailable  Indicates that no provider is available to service the given request.
LcsInvalidInvokation  Indicates one of the following: Application has sent an invalid invoke id in the MT-LR response The interface is not valid for the selected transport protocol The application is sending a 2nd MO-LR which is not allowed The application is trying to abort a non-existent self-location request
LcsGltpConnSetupFailure  Indicates a failure in setting up the GPRS connection to the GL server.
LcsGltpTimeOut  Indicates a time-out occurrence waiting for an acknowledgment from the GL server.
LcsGltpSendFailure  Indicates a failure to send the request to the GL server.
LcsGltpInvalidData  Indicates that invalid data received from the GL server or Lcs stack.
LcsGltpMolrInProgress  Indicates that a MO-LR is already in progress.
